You can check the Scipy webpage dedicated to Windows install, where you can
find some information about installing a compiler, and the BLAS library.
See https://www.scipy.org/scipylib/building/windows.html

A second option is to use the Anaconda Python distribution
(available at <https://docs.anaconda.com/anaconda/>) and the corresponding
SPAMS package designed for Anaconda.

You can contact us if you encounter any trouble.
